    "tags": "solitary, large",
    "qualities": "<p><strong>Iron hide</strong> (Armor 4, unnatural resilience): a hit dealing 2 or less damage before armor chips or shatters the weapon. Always hungry, easily provoked, and afraid of fire.</p>",
    "count": 1,
    "entry": "",
    "notes": "",
    "creatureType": "natural-beast",
    "description": "<p>When a boar lives long enough, survives enough close calls, and dines year after year on the roots and nuts of ferro trees, it eventually becomes a raselbaedd: the size of a horse, with tusks like short spears and a hide crisscrossed with scars and bristling with broken blades. Its hide (immobile, Value 2) can be harvested by a competent hunter with a fine steel blade and fashioned into 1d4 raselbaedd cuirasses (2 armor, Value 3).</p>",
